IF CONDITIONS 
1) Print largest and smallest values out of two
a, b = 10, 5
if a > b: print("Largest:", a, "Smallest:", b)
else: print("Largest:", b, "Smallest:", a)

Output: Largest: 10 Smallest: 5

 2) Print largest and smallest values out of three
a, b, c = 10, 15, 5
if a > b and a > c: print("Largest:", a)
elif b > c: print("Largest:", b)
else: print("Largest:", c)

if a < b and a < c: print("Smallest:", a)
elif b < c: print("Smallest:", b)
else: print("Smallest:", c)

 Output: Largest: 15 Smallest: 5

3) Check whether a given number is odd or even
number = 7
if number % 2 == 0: print("Even")
else: print("Odd")

Output: Odd

4) Check whether a given number is divisible by 10 or not
number = 20
if number % 10 == 0: print("Divisible by 10")
else: print("Not divisible by 10")

Output: Divisible by 10

5) Accept age of a person. If age is less than 18, print minor otherwise Major age = 20
if age < 18: print("Minor")
else: print("Major")
Output: Major

6) Accept a number from the user. And print number of digits in it
number = 12345
print("Number of digits:", len(str(abs(number))))

Output: Number of digits: 5

 7) Accept a year value from the user. Check whether it is a leap year or not
year = 2024
if (year % 4 == 0 and year % 100 != 0) or (year % 400 == 0): print("Leap Year")
else: print("Not a Leap Year")

 Output: Leap Year

 8) Check whether a triangle is valid or not when the three angles of the triangle are entered
a, b, c = 60, 60, 60
if a + b + c == 180: print("Valid Triangle")
else: print("Invalid Triangle")

Output: Valid Triangle

 9) Print absolute value of a given number
number = -5
print("Absolute Value:", abs(number))

 Output: Absolute Value: 5

10) Given the length and breadth of a rectangle, find whether the area is greater than perimeter
length, breadth = 6, 4
area = length * breadth
perimeter = 2 * (length + breadth)
if area > perimeter: print("Area is greater than perimeter")
else: print("Perimeter is greater than or equal to area")

 Output: Area is greater than perimeter

 11) Check if three points fall on one straight line
x1, y1, x2, y2, x3, y3 = 0, 0, 1, 1, 2, 2
if (y2 - y1) * (x3 - x2) == (y3 - y2) * (x2 - x1): print("Points are on one straight line")
else: print("Points are not on one straight line")

Output: Points are on one straight line

 12) Check if a point lies inside, on, or outside the circle
cx, cy, radius, px, py = 0, 0, 5, 3, 3
distance = ((px - cx)**2 + (py - cy)**2)**0.5
if distance < radius: print("Point is inside the circle")
elif distance == radius: print("Point is on the circle")
else: print("Point is outside the circle")

 Output: Point is inside the circle

13) Convert number 0 to 19 to its equivalent words
number = 19
words = ["zero", "one", "two", "three", "four", "five", "six", "seven", "eight", "nine", "ten",
         "eleven", "twelve", "thirteen", "fourteen", "fifteen", "sixteen", "seventeen", "eighteen", "nineteen"]
if 0 <= number <= 19: print(words[number])

 Output: nineteen

14) Accept marks of three subjects and determine status, average, and grades
marks = [85, 40, 39]
total = sum(marks)
average = total / len(marks)
status = "Pass"
grades = []
for mark in marks:
    if mark <= 39: grades.append("F"); status = "Fail"
    elif mark <= 44: grades.append("P")
    elif mark <= 49: grades.append("C")
    elif mark <= 54: grades.append("B")
    elif mark <= 59: grades.append("B+")
    elif mark <= 69: grades.append("A")
    elif mark <= 79: grades.append("A+")
    elif mark <= 100: grades.append("O")
    else: grades.append("NA")
print("Total Marks:", total, "Average Marks:", average, "Status:", status, "Grades:", grades)

Output: Total Marks: 164 Average Marks: 54.666666666666664 Status: Fail Grades: ['O', 'P', 'F']
